          "description": "Inside Atmos plotter||||||\u0026lt;br\u0026gt;\u0026lt;font color\u003d\u0026quot;red\u0026quot;\u0026gt;\u0026lt;strong\u0026gt;\u0026gt;\u0026nbsp;INSIDE ATMOS PLOTTER\u0026lt;/strong\u0026gt;\u0026lt;/font\u0026gt;\u0026lt;br\u0026gt;\u0026lt;blockquote\u0026gt;The MCP-40 plotter uses a Japanese printing mechanism manufactured by Sharp. It\u0027s a little mechanical marvel able to print extremely precise four colour texts and graphics. Text is printed with 40 or 80 characters per line, at 10 characters per second speed. Characters size and  printing direction may be modified (horizontal, vertical or diagonal). \u0026lt;br\u0026gt;\u0026lt;br\u0026gt;  \u0026lt;b\u0026gt;(1)\u0026lt;/b\u0026gt; Paper used is a roller of 115 mm width.\u0026lt;br\u0026gt; \u0026lt;b\u0026gt;(2)\u0026lt;/b\u0026gt; Printer command buttons.\u0026lt;br\u0026gt; \u0026lt;b\u0026gt;(3)\u0026lt;/b\u0026gt; Electromagnet that pushes the pen against paper for writing.\u0026lt;br\u0026gt; \u0026lt;b\u0026gt;(4)\u0026lt;/b\u0026gt; The print head moves laterally right across the paper width and swivels to carry out a pen colour change.\u0026lt;br\u0026gt; \u0026lt;b\u0026gt;(5)\u0026lt;/b\u0026gt; The head is connected through a cable to an engine which ensures its side moving by 0.2 mm steps.\u0026lt;br\u0026gt; \u0026lt;b\u0026gt;(6)\u0026lt;/b\u0026gt; A second engine controls top and bottom paper moving, also by 0.2 mm steps.\u0026lt;/blockquote\u0026gt;"
        }
